    <p>The Lovelace textbook covers language acquisition, syntactic parsing, and semantic composition in addition to the information-theoretic and pragmatic perspectives presented here. This page focuses on the three ideas that connect most directly to the computational toolkit: surprisal as a linking hypothesis between models and reading data, n-gram models as the simplest language model, and RSA as Bayesian inference applied to communication.</p>

